    <title>Hilary Duff says the Lizzie McGuire Disney Plus series is officially dead</title>
    <content type="html">  

    &lt;figure&gt;
      &lt;img alt="" src="https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/yOFqhDRvPwgQopkwvyfYuQGjp6c=/74x0:649x383/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/68526670/lizzie_mcguire_lizzie_and_gordo_photo_e1574211145930.0.jpg" /&gt;
        &lt;figcaption&gt;&lt;em&gt;Image: Disney&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/figcaption&gt;
    &lt;/figure&gt;

  &lt;p id="LBhTYK"&gt;The &lt;em&gt;Lizzie McGuire&lt;/em&gt; Disney Plus series is officially dead, according to an &lt;a href="https://www.instagram.com/p/CI3x83hDMYt/"&gt;Instagram post&lt;/a&gt; from Hilary Duff. The series was reportedly going to feature an adult Duff reprising her role as Lizzie in her 30s, navigating a career in New York, and dealing with more “adult” themes. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p id="L3Rlvz"&gt;“It’s been an honor to have Lizzie in my life,” Duff wrote. “I know the efforts and conversations have been everywhere trying to make work, but sadly and despite everyone’s best efforts [the reboot] isn’t going to happen.”&lt;/p&gt;
